Abstract = {This work describes a hardware architecture implementation of an
   associative memory neural network (AMNN) using reconfigurable hardware
   devices such as FPGA (Field Programmable Gates Arrays) and its
   applications in image pattern recognition systems. An associative memory
   is a content-addressable structure that maps specific input
   representations to specific output representations. It is a system that
   ``associates{''} two patterns (X, Y) such that when one is encountered,
   the other can be recalled. In the design, learning and recognizing
   algorithms for the neural network are implemented by using VHSIC
   Hardware Description Language. FPGA is used for implementation because
   they can reduce development time greatly, ease of fast reprogramming,
   low price, flexible architecture and permitting fast and non expensive
   implementation of the whole system. The architecture was evaluated as
